**Expressionalism: A Unified Formal Model of Relational Obtainability, Secondary Synthesis, and the Tension of Certainty**

This appendix supplies the complete, unified mathematical articulation of the Expressionalism framework. It functions as the primary technical reference for all formal modeling, metrics, and operational procedures employed across Presumptions 1–8. The framework takes expression — understood as any provisional stabilization of secondary synthesis — as its fundamental primitive. Pointing is the directed, representational, or reflexive aspect of an expression: its capacity to stabilize toward itself, toward distinct repeatable entities, or toward what resists connection. The present formalization models every quantity as a continuous spectrum or gradient valued in the closed unit interval \[0,1\], reported to a precision of 0.001. This choice enacts the framework’s commitment to graded, non-binary distinctions while preserving computational tractability and auditability.

The distinctions articulated in this mathematical model emerge within the activity of analyzing an expression that has already obtained. They do not function as ontological prerequisites that must obtain before any expression can occur. The framework therefore maintains ontological neutrality with respect to substantive metaphysical commitments. Like every other component of the schema, this mathematical model remains fully provisional and subject to revision, extension, or replacement under Presumption 8\.

This formal model supplies the general mathematical machinery — hybrid functions, fuzzy membership families, normalized Bayesian posteriors, dilemma gates, and inheritance rules — from which the concrete metrics, phases, and ledgers of the Expressionalism Toolkit are derived as operational specializations. Every specific implementation choice in the toolkit (including the precise weighting of the Secondary Coherence Score, the log-odds formulation of the Inferred Relator Mode Distribution, uncertainty clamping rules, and binomial falsification thresholds) remains fully consistent with the general principles articulated here and is subject to the same renewal logic under Presumption 8\.

