## **11\. Status and Revisability**

This mathematical model articulates one coherent formalization of the functional distinctions developed across Presumptions 1–8. It supplies operational precision and computational tractability for secondary synthesis audits, metric derivation, and toolkit implementation. Secondary synthesis remains the operative engine through which primary expressions obtain their standing.

It does not claim to describe what existence must be like independent of analysis, nor does it privilege relational connectivity as more fundamental than what resists it. Non-relational gaps are treated as strict limit concepts and remainders of expressions where secondary synthesis fails or is refused. The model registers only the points at which resistance appears as a loss of traction and maintains consistent operational restraint in further interpretive gestures.

Because every engagement with this mathematical model — including the decision to adopt, revise, extend, replace, or set it aside — itself constitutes an expression, the entire formal apparatus remains subject to the renewal logic of Presumption 8\. Analysts may strengthen, weaken, replace, or bypass any component of this model as part of a new primary expression. The framework therefore carries its own mechanism of self-correction from the outset and makes no claim to final or canonical status.

The Open Field stays open. The renewal loop remains open.

